ENTRY       EC 1.3.1.85                 Enzyme
NAME        crotonyl-CoA carboxylase/reductase;
            CCR;
            crotonyl-CoA reductase (carboxylating)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-CH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     (2S)-ethylmalonyl-CoA:NADP+ oxidoreductase (decarboxylating)
REACTION    (2S)-ethylmalonyl-CoA + NADP+ = (E)-but-2-enoyl-CoA + CO2 + NADPH + H+ [RN:R09291]
ALL_REAC    R09291
SUBSTRATE   (2S)-ethylmalonyl-CoA [CPD:C18026];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     (E)-but-2-enoyl-CoA [CPD:C00877];
            CO2 [CPD:C00011];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The reaction is catalysed in the reverse direction. This enzyme, isolated from the bacterium Rhodobacter sphaeroides, catalyses (E)-but-2-enoyl-CoA-dependent oxidation of NADPH in the presence of CO2. When CO2 is absent, the enzyme catalyses the reduction of (E)-but-2-enoyl-CoA to butanoyl-CoA, but with only 10% of maximal activity (relative to (E)-but-2-enoyl-CoA carboxylation).
